articular, we completely resolve the $n=3$ case of a\nquestion raised in 2001 by Xingzhi Zhan. As an application, we extend previous\nwork by de Pillis [Duke Math. J. 36] by classifying the characters $K$ of the\ncomplex plane for which the map $(H_{st})_{s,t=1}^n \\mapsto (K({\\rm\ntr}(H_{st})))_{s,t=1}^n$ preserves positivity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 27 Apr 2014 23:03:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-04-29"}
